Review complete. Saved 5 findings to `CHI-14_review.md`:

| # | Type | Line | Severity | Issue |
|---|------|------|----------|-------|
| 1 | BUG | 365 | High | `Hijack()` delegates to compression writer instead of `ResponseWriter` — always fails when compression is active |
| 2 | BUG | 372 | High | `Push()` same issue — delegates to encoder, not the HTTP/2 connection |
| 3 | BUG | 249 | Medium | `matchAcceptEncoding` uses `strings.Contains` (substring match) instead of token comparison — e.g. `"br"` falsely matches `"brotli"` |
| 4 | BUG | 183-186 | Low | Slice mutated during `range` without `break` — can skip/duplicate elements |
| 5 | QUESTION | 348-361 | Low | `Flush()` may double-flush custom encoders that implement both `http.Flusher` and `compressFlusher` |

**Assessment: FIX FIRST** — The Hijack/Push bugs break HTTP features under compression.
